  "text": "Three main limits of these approaches can be identified. Firstly, it is hard to see how these methods could be applied on environments that are different from MuJoCo, which seems adequate to these methods since the agent often falls in the same state (on the floor) when the goal is uninteresting. Secondly, the agent is unable to learn to generate goals without unlearning its skills. This way, the goal distribution generated by the agent has to stay uniform [CITATION_1] . Thirdly, none of these approaches tries to use a continuous embedding of trajectories.",
